# Ghiath - agent configuration (template).
#
# Copy this to agents.conf and edit it. agents.conf is gitignored, so your
# personal agent names and model choices never land in the public repo:
#
#   cp agents.conf.example agents.conf
#
# This file is sourced (not parsed) by scripts/hermes.sh, so it is plain shell:
# NAME=value, no spaces around '='. Anything you set here overrides the
# defaults baked into the scripts. Secrets stay in .env, not here.
#
# There are exactly two agents, one per side of life. They are fully isolated:
# separate hermes profiles, separate vaults, separate Qdrant collections,
# separate Telegram bots. There are no handoffs and no router between them.

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Work assistant - yours alone. Technical work, one capable model.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# NAME becomes the profile's CLI alias command. MODEL is the slug KeiRouter
# serves. PORT is the gateway it listens on. VAULT is the Obsidian folder
# (relative to the repo root) it owns, and COLLECTION its Qdrant collection.
WORK_NAME="work"
WORK_MODEL="z-ai/glm-5.1"
WORK_PORT="8642"
WORK_VAULT="vault-work"
WORK_COLLECTION="vault_work"

# The work agent asks for confirmation over Telegram before it executes a
# technical task. Set to 0 to let it act immediately instead.
WORK_CONFIRM_GATE="1"

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Home assistant - shared with the household. Everyday tasks, fast cheap model.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
HOME_NAME="home"
HOME_MODEL="deepseek/deepseek-v4-flash"
HOME_PORT="8645"
HOME_VAULT="vault-home"
HOME_COLLECTION="vault_home"

# Telegram bot tokens are secrets and live in .env, not here:
#   WORK_TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN   (or TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN) -> the work agent
#   HOME_TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN                           -> the home agent
# They are two SEPARATE @BotFather bots, so the household bot can never reach
# your work vault.
